The paper focuses on generating novel views of large-scale scenes, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) applications. The proposed method also incorporates inverse depth features obtained from CNNs, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of adversarial loss for improving image quality suggests a possible connection to generative models (cs.GR).
